{
  "text": "The translation of ψ is the λ-term ψ , displayed in the middle of Figure 23 . This term has two normal forms (corresponding to S ω and P ω ), as indicated in the figure. In [CITATION_1] positive CR ∞ results are mentioned for Böhm Tree normal forms in λ ∞ βη-calculus. ",
  "correct_citation": {
